      "content": "No specific mathematical justification exists for purely non-random temperature bursts in climate models if they lack physical forcing drivers. These patterns often stem from artifacts such as unbalanced boundary conditions, localized physics scheme failures (like cloud microphysics or convection parameterization), or pre-processing errors in your diagnostic data. Since I cannot verify your specific model code or land masks, please investigate whether your topographical inputs have coordinate mismatches or if your physics parameters below those thresholds are triggering erroneous convective overshoots.",
